ime of disk parameters that reproduces observed M-dwarf systems such as TRAPPIST-1. However, giant planets around late M dwarfs, such as GJ 3512b, only form when type I migration is substantially reduced. {$<$}BR /{$>$} Conclusions: We are able to quantify the stellar mass dependence of multi-planet systems using global simulations of planet formation and evolution. The results fare well in comparison to current observational data and predict trends that can be tested with future observations. {$<$}P /{$>$}The data supporting these findings are available online at {$<$}A href="http://dace.unige.ch"{$>$}http://dace.unige.ch{$<$}/A{$>$} under section "Formation \&amp; Evolution".},
