  year = {2020},
  abstract = {We report the discovery and validation of four extrasolar planets hosted by the nearby, bright, Sun-like (G3V) star HD{$\sim$}108236 using data from the Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS). We present transit photometry, reconnaissance and precise Doppler spectroscopy as well as high-resolution imaging, to validate the planetary nature of the objects transiting HD{$\sim$}108236, also known as the TESS Object of Interest (TOI) 1233. The innermost planet is a possibly-rocky super-Earth with a period of \$3.79523\_\{-0.00044\}\^\{+0.00047\}\$ days and has a radius of \$1.586\textbackslash backslashpm0.098\$ \$R\_\textbackslash backslashoplus\$. The outer planets are sub-Neptunes, with potential gaseous envelopes, having radii of \$2.068\_\{-0.091\}\^\{+0.10\}\$ \$R\_\textbackslash backslashoplus\$, \$2.72\textbackslash backslashpm0.11\$ \$R\_\textbackslash backslashoplus\$, and \$3.12\_\{-0.12\}\^\{+0.13\}\$ \$R\_\textbackslash backslashoplus\$ and periods of \$6.20370\_\{-0.00052\}\^\{+0.00064\}\$ days, \$14.17555\_\{-0.0011\}\^\{+0.00099\}\$ days, and \$19.5917\_\{-0.0020\}\^\{+0.0022\}\$ days, respectively. With V and K\$\_\{\textbackslash backslashrm s\}\$ magnitudes of 9.2 and 7.6, respectively, the bright host star makes the transiting planets favorable targets for mass measurements and, potentially, for atmospheric characterization via transmission spectroscopy. HD{$\sim$}108236 is the brightest Sun-like star in the visual (V) band known to host four or more transiting exoplanets. The discovered planets span a broad range of planetary radii and equilibrium temperatures, and share a common history of insolation from a Sun-like star (\$R\_\textbackslash backslashstar = 0.888 \textbackslash backslashpm 0.017\$ R\$\_\textbackslash backslashodot\$, \$T\_\{\textbackslash backslashrm eff\} = 5730 \textbackslash backslashpm 50\$ K), making HD 108236 an exciting, opportune cosmic laboratory for testing models of planet formation and evolution.},
  keywords = {atmospheres,discovery,hd 108236,hip 60689,individual,tess,tic 260647166,toi 1233,tyc id 8243-01948-1},
