in the case of low mass stars. This is because for \$M\_\textbackslash backslashstar\textbackslash textless1\textbackslash backslash,M\_\textbackslash backslashodot\$, the observed \$M\_\{\textbackslash backslashrm\{dust\}\}\$ obtained from models is very low due to the efficient growth of dust particles beyond centimeter sizes (boulders) inside pressure bumps.},
