sis, suggesting that it might be remnant eccentricity from its migration. The longest period planet in this sample, TOI-1478 b (P = 10.18 days), is a warm Jupiter in a circular orbit around a near-Solar analogue. NASA's \$TESS\$ mission is continuing to increase the sample of well-characterized hot and warm Jupiters, complementing its primary mission goals.},
